  "prompt": "How much money did each candidate spend in the 1912 election?",
  "response": "In the 1912 U.S. presidential election, the major candidates were Woodrow Wilson (Democrat), Theodore Roosevelt (Progressive), and William Howard Taft (Republican). The campaign expenditures for each candidate were as follows:\n\n- **Woodrow Wilson**: Approximately $1.1 million\n- **Theodore Roosevelt**: Around $2.5 million\n- **William Howard Taft**: About $900,000\n\nThese amounts reflect the spending in a time when campaign financing was significantly different from today's standards. Roosevelt's campaign, representing the Progressive Party, was particularly notable for being well-funded compared to his competitors.",
